Each device connected to the phone is included in the maximum device count. For example, the USB port on your phone can support a maximum of five USB devices (such as three Cisco Unified IP Color Key Expansion modules, one hub, and one other standard USB device). Many third-party USB products count as multiple USB devices, for example, a device containing USB hub and headset can count as two USB devices. For more information, see the USB device documentation.
